  "what": "Hour-of-day activity curve, measured over the lake. The off-hours band that fact_auth_event.is_off_hours and warehouse Q2 use is DERIVED from this measurement \u2014 it is never assumed.",
  "caveat": "LANL ships relative seconds, not wall-clock time; hour = (t mod 86400) // 3600, so hour labels are offsets from the start of collection rather than certified local clock hours. The SHAPE of the curve is a real measurement. That the human trough lands on hours 00-05 and the peak on 07-15 is itself evidence that t=0 sits near local midnight \u2014 but that is an inference from the data, not something LANL documents, and nothing in Tarn depends on it being exactly right.",
  "key_finding": "Machine accounts run around the clock and are the bulk of the traffic, which flattens the aggregate curve to a peak:trough of 1.46x and hides the cycle entirely. Human accounts alone show 1.79x, with a clean overnight trough. Splitting them is what makes an off-hours claim defensible at all.",
